Questions for 10 Trees Team

**How the System Will Be Used**

1.  Each household already receives a small smartphone - do you know
    which models or screen size they have? They vary quite a bit. Most
    are cheaper versions (Nokia, or off brands)

2.  How well do those phones work for short tasks now (for example,
    filling out WhatsApp forms or viewing photos)? Again, quite
    variable. They don't fill out forms on WhatsApp. They take photos
    and send messages.

3.  Do you think it would work best to:

    a.  Keep using those phones and design the forms to fit small
        screens,

    b.  Get a few shared larger phones or tablets for mentors to help
        households, or

    c.  Use a mix (women answer questions, mentors enter data)? This is
        what happens now. The mentors do the surveys and submit the data
        to our admin person who enters it into an Excel spread sheet.
        Currently there are 17 mentors in Orpen Gate Village.

4.  If new devices might help, how many would make a real difference
    without stretching your budget? We don't have a budget for any new
    devices but maybe we could find someone/some people to donate them.
    It would be great if they all were on the same device.

5.  The Centre has Wi-Fi - is there any mobile data coverage in the
    villages? We provide data for each tree mentor. No one else has
    wifi. Network is a bit sketchy and goes down quite often.

6.  Would it make sense for mentors to collect forms offline and then
    upload them at the Centre, or do some have enough data to submit
    directly from the field? Depends on how much data it will take to
    submit. Right now they turn in their garden assessments at the
    Centre so it could happen there.

7.  Who do you picture actually filling in the forms most often - the
    women, the mentors, or Centre staff helping later? The mentors fill
    in the forms.

